                                   "A reference value is a controlled, enumerated value used to classify or qualify other entities in the knowledge graph, such as access types, platforms, quality metrics, or product types. Reference values provide semantic consistency without introducing additional domain entities."@en ;
                   dp:embedding_note "Reference Value has definition A controlled vocabulary value used to classify and describe catalog assets. Reference values represent stable pick-list style terms (for example, Access Types, Platforms, and other catalog classifications)."@en ,
                                     "Reference Value has definition A reference value is a controlled, enumerated value used to classify or qualify other entities in the knowledge graph, such as access types, platforms, quality metrics, or product types. Reference values provide semantic consistency without introducing additional domain entities."@en .


