###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_01
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_01 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 1 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """The Creator Insights Aggregation produces the SF Creator Insights Dataset, a curated table of creator KPIs used by dashboards, reporting, and downstream metric computations. It consolidates engagement events into creator-level aggregates and applies standard filters, normalization, and windowing.

Primary output: SF Creator Insights Dataset.
Secondary outputs: run metadata, validation summaries, and intermediate aggregates used for debugging."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Purpose and outputs"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 01"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 01 has title Purpose and outputs."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_02
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_02 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 2 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Inputs:
- Engagement Events Dataset (event stream, normalized)
- Video Metadata Dataset (video → creator mapping and content attributes)
- Creator Profile Dataset (creator reference data and eligibility flags)

All three inputs are required. If any input fails freshness thresholds, the run is considered degraded and must not publish outputs to production dashboards."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Inputs"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 02"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 02 has title Inputs."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_03
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_03 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 3 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """High-level transformation steps:
1) Filter engagement events to eligible events and valid account/video ids.
2) Join events to video metadata to map events to creators.
3) Join to creator profile reference data (tier, region, account status).
4) Aggregate by creator and reporting window to compute KPIs (plays, unique viewers, engagement rate, etc.).
5) Normalize and apply standard definitions (e.g., deduping retry bursts).
6) Publish curated results to SF Creator Insights Dataset."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Transformations (high-level)"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 03"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 03 has title Transformations (high-level)."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_04
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_04 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 4 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Quality checks include:
- Completeness of joins (event→video, video→creator)
- Distribution checks on key metrics (outliers, zeros, negative values)
- Volume regression checks (unexpected drops/spikes by region)
- Schema conformance validation

Failure handling:
- Hard failures stop the run.
- Soft failures publish output to a quarantine location and alert the Analytics Engineering Team."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Quality checks"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 04"@en ;
                                                        docs:has_topic skos:ConceptScheme ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 04 has title Quality checks."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_05
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_05 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 5 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Provenance is recorded using PROV-O:
- The aggregation run is a prov:Activity (dp:Data_Analysis_Activity).
- Input datasets are prov:Entity assets.
- Output dataset is generated by the activity.
- The Analytics Engineering Team is associated with the activity.

This structure enables automated embedding-note generation and supports question answering such as: 'What datasets were used to produce SF Creator Insights?' and 'Which team ran the aggregation?'"""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Provenance and traceability"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 05"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 05 has title Provenance and traceability."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_06
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_06 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 6 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Schedule: the aggregation is typically run daily, with additional ad-hoc runs during major product launches.

Operational constraints:
- Completion time target: under 30 minutes.
- Freshness requirements: engagement events must be available within a defined latency window.
- Publishing rules: do not overwrite prior snapshots without a version identifier.

If SLAs are missed, downstream metrics (e.g., Creator Growth) may be stale for dashboards."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Operational schedule and SLAs"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 06"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 06 has title Operational schedule and SLAs."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_07
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_07 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 7 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Common failure modes:
- Partial ingestion of engagement events causing artificial volume drops
- Missing video metadata due to upstream schema change
- Creator reference data drift (stale account status)
- Unexpected spikes from client retry storms

Mitigation:
- Validate input dataset freshness and schema before running aggregation.
- Use regression checks on event volumes and join completeness.
- Maintain a rollback plan for publishing outputs."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Common failure modes"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 07"@en ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 07 has title Common failure modes."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_08
docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_08 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                 docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                        docs:chunk_index 8 ;
                                                        docs:chunk_text """Downstream consumers include:
- Executive dashboards that display creator KPIs
- Metric computations such as Creator Growth
- Ad-hoc analyses (demographics, regional trends)

Because downstream systems assume stable KPI definitions, changes to the aggregation logic must be coordinated via a data contract and communicated to consumers before deployment."""@en ;
                                                        docs:chunk_title "Downstream dependencies"@en ;
                                                        rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 08"@en ;
                                                        docs:has_topic dp:Contract ;
                                                        dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 08 has title Downstream dependencies."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Incident_Report ;
                                                         docs:uses_data_product dp:SF_Video_Metadata_Product ;
                                                         docs:uses_dataset sf:Video_Metadata_Current ;
                                                         dctm:created "2025-09-03"^^xsd:date ;
                                                         dctm:creator "Data Reliability Engineering (DRE)"@en ;
                                                         dctm:publisher "StreamForge Platform Operations"@en ;
                                                         dctm:title "Incident Report — Video Metadata Freshness Regression"@en ;
                                                         rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression"@en ;
                                                         dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression has creator Data Reliability Engineering (DRE)."@en ,
                                                                           "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression has publisher StreamForge Platform Operations."@en ,
                                                                           "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression is an instance of Incident Report."@en ,
                                                                           "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression uses data product SF Video Metadata Product."@en ,
                                                                           "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression uses dataset Video Metadata Current."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_01
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_01 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 1 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "On 2025-09-01 a regression in video metadata freshness caused the cataloged metadata dataset to lag real-time updates by several hours. The incident affected personalization cold-start behavior and search indexing for newly uploaded videos. This report documents impact, timeline, root cause, and corrective actions."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Summary"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 01"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 01 has title Summary."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_02
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_02 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 2 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "Window of impact: 2025-09-01 08:20 UTC to 2025-09-01 16:05 UTC. Metadata lag: up to 6.4 hours at peak. User impact: reduced impressions and slower indexing for new uploads; elevated not relevant feedback in new-content cohorts. Internal impact: downstream jobs consumed stale timestamps, triggering feature drift alerts."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Impact"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 02"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 02 has title Impact."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_03
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_03 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 3 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "Primary signal: freshness SLA monitor breached for the Video Metadata dataset. Secondary signal: downstream model feature drift alerts spiked for timestamp-derived features."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Detection"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 03"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 03 has title Detection."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_04
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_04 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 4 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "08:20 freshness SLA breach detected. 08:35 incident declared; DRE engaged. 09:10 suspected backlog in ingestion pipeline. 11:40 identified retry storm in metadata enrichment. 13:15 mitigation applied by throttling retries and clearing stuck partitions. 16:05 freshness returned to normal; incident resolved."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Timeline (UTC)"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 04"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 04 has title Timeline (UTC)."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_05
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_05 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 5 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "A deployment changed retry behavior in the metadata enrichment job. Malformed payloads triggered repeated retries, saturating the queue and delaying partitions. The system lacked a circuit breaker for repeated failures on the same payload class."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Root cause"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 05"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 05 has title Root cause."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_06
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_06 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 6 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "Add circuit breaker and dead-letter routing for malformed payloads. Rate-limit retries and cap max retry time per partition. Introduce payload validation earlier in ingestion."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Corrective actions (engineering controls)"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 06"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 06 has title Corrective actions (engineering controls)."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_07
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_07 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 7 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "Extend catalog checks to include freshness monotonicity and timestamp plausibility rules."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Corrective actions (catalog checks)"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 07"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 07 has title Corrective actions (catalog checks)."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_08
docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_08 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                           docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_index 8 ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_text "Owner: Video Metadata data product team. Deadline: implement circuit breaker and catalog validation rules by 2025-09-20. Verification: replay incident window and confirm SLA compliance under fault injection."@en ;
                                                                  docs:chunk_title "Follow-up"@en ;
                                                                  rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 08"@en ;
                                                                  dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 08 has title Follow-up."@en .


